        <h1>16<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Display template</h1>
        <div class="figure"><a name="_1ac76e94-0932-411e-8186-f6591d8b0716" id="_1ac76e94-0932-411e-8186-f6591d8b0716"></a>

<p class="figure" style="page-break-after:avoid;"><img src="iso-19160-6_files/e702c594-fccf-4073-af03-bf09340e6a7a.png" height="270" width="400"/></p>
<p class="FigureTitle" style="text-align:center;">Figure 12&#xA0;&#x2014; Display template data model</p></div>
        <div><a name="872d2595-d899-49da-8033-0c7b4d175189" id="872d2595-d899-49da-8033-0c7b4d175189"></a><h2>16.1<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>DisplayTemplate</h2>

</div>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_e103a7b8-cc5a-4784-a1f7-3b67f92432db" id="_e103a7b8-cc5a-4784-a1f7-3b67f92432db"></a>The display template is used for displaying an
interchange address instance belonging to an interchange
address class. Generally, one address class is represented
by one display template.</p>
        <div><a name="9a9078ca-5b55-4fab-87e1-d3d5e108d5b8" id="9a9078ca-5b55-4fab-87e1-d3d5e108d5b8"></a><h2>16.2<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>DisplayLine</h2>

